description.p:
Examples of C-arylglucoside (also referred to as C-glucosides) SGLT2 inhibitors, include, but are not limited to, the following:


1) C-aryl glucosides as disclosed in U.S. Patent Nos. 6,515,117 and 6,414,126;

2) C-aryl glucosides as described in U.S. Patent Application No. 11/233617 (U.S. Patent Application Publication No. 2006/0063722 A1);

3) C-aryl glucosides described in U.S. Patent No. 6,774,112;

4) Glucopyranosyl-substituted benzene derivatives as disclosed in U.S. Patent Application Publication No. 2005/0209166; and

5) D-pyranosyl-substituted phenyl compounds as disclosed in U.S. Patent Application Publication No. S 2006/0074031.

Examples of O-glucoside SGLT2 inhibitors include, but are not limited to, those described in the following:


1) 5-Thio-β-D-glucopyranoside as disclosed in U.S. Patent Application Publication No. 2006/0194809;

2) Glucopyranyloxybenzene derivatives as disclosed in WO 03/01180;

3) Pyrazole derivatives as disclosed in U.S. Patent No. 6,908,905; and

4) Pyrazole compounds as disclosed in U.S. Patent No. 6,815,428.
